speciesData.name: Turtwig
speciesData.flavor_text:
It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making
oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

speciesData.name: Grotle
speciesData.flavor_text:
It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow
Pokémon there on its back.

speciesData.name: Torterra
speciesData.flavor_text:
Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving
back to begin building their nests.

speciesData.name: Chimchar
speciesData.flavor_text:
The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end.
The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

speciesData.name: Monferno
speciesData.flavor_text:
It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks.
Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

speciesData.name: Infernape
speciesData.flavor_text:
It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all
its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

speciesData.name: Piplup
speciesData.flavor_text:
Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food
from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

speciesData.name: Prinplup
speciesData.flavor_text:
It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows
that can snap even the thickest of trees.

speciesData.name: Empoleon
speciesData.flavor_text:
The three horns that extend from its beak attest to
its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

speciesData.name: Starly
speciesData.flavor_text:
They flock around mountains and fields, chasing
after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy
and annoying.

speciesData.name: Staravia
speciesData.flavor_text:
It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over
territory occur when flocks collide.

speciesData.name: Staraptor
speciesData.flavor_text:
When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the
flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

speciesData.name: Bidoof
speciesData.flavor_text:
It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle
down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

speciesData.name: Bibarel
speciesData.flavor_text:
It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and
mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

speciesData.name: Kricketot
speciesData.flavor_text:
When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the
music of a xylophone.

speciesData.name: Kricketune
speciesData.flavor_text:
It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists
are studying these melodic patterns.

speciesData.name: Shinx
speciesData.flavor_text:
All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees
while the foe is momentarily blinded.

speciesData.name: Luxio
speciesData.flavor_text:
Strong electricity courses through the tips of its
sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

speciesData.name: Luxray
speciesData.flavor_text:
Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in
handy when it’s scouting for danger.

speciesData.name: Budew
speciesData.flavor_text:
Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the
cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

speciesData.name: Roserade
speciesData.flavor_text:
With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with
whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

speciesData.name: Cranidos
speciesData.flavor_text:
In rock layers where Cranidos fossils are found,
the fossilized trunks of trees snapped in two
are also often found.

speciesData.name: Rampardos
speciesData.flavor_text:
Records exist of a revived fossil that evolved
into Rampardos. It proceeded to escape and
then destroy a skyscraper with a headbutt.

speciesData.name: Shieldon
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles. Few
enemies would have been willing to square off
against its heavily armored face, so it’s thought.

speciesData.name: Bastiodon
speciesData.flavor_text:
It lived in the same environments as Rampardos.
Their fossils have been found together—
seemingly from after they’d fought to the finish.

form_descriptions.description: Forms only affect appearance, although they become permanent upon evolution.  Wild and newly-hatched Burmy are always in a Plant Cloak.  Burmy's cloak changes to match the terrain after a battle it participated in: Plant Cloak by default; Sandy Cloak in sandy or rocky areas, such as beaches, caves, and trails; and Trash Cloak in buildings.

speciesData.name: Burmy
speciesData.flavor_text:
If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes
the cloak with materials nearby.

form_descriptions.description: Forms have different stats and movepools.  During evolution, Burmy's current cloak becomes Wormadam's form, and can no longer be changed.

speciesData.name: Wormadam
speciesData.flavor_text:
When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of
this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

speciesData.name: Mothim
speciesData.flavor_text:
It flutters around at night and steals honey from
the Combee hive.

speciesData.name: Combee
speciesData.flavor_text:
It collects and delivers honey to its colony.
At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

speciesData.name: Vespiquen
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its
grubs on honey collected by Combee.

speciesData.name: Pachirisu
speciesData.flavor_text:
A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches
together in an effort to share stored electricity.

speciesData.name: Buizel
speciesData.flavor_text:
It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and
pokes its head out of the water to see what is
going on.

speciesData.name: Floatzel
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing
aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

speciesData.name: Cherubi
speciesData.flavor_text:
It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small
ball where it had been storing nutrients.

form_descriptions.description: Sunshine form is active during strong sunlight.  Otherwise, Cherrim defaults to its Overcast form.

speciesData.name: Cherrim
speciesData.flavor_text:
If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded
petals to absorb the sun’s rays with its whole body.

form_descriptions.description: Forms only affect appearance.  A form is determined before a wild encounter based on whether the battle is in western or eastern Sinnoh, or inherited from the mother when breeding, and cannot be changed.

speciesData.name: Shellos
speciesData.flavor_text:
Purple mucus sticks to the hands of anyone
who touches it. Take care, as the substance is
troublesome to wash off.

form_descriptions.description: Forms only affect appearance.  A form is determined before a wild encounter based on whether the battle is in western or eastern Sinnoh and cannot be changed.

speciesData.name: Gastrodon
speciesData.flavor_text:
Plankton, invisible to the naked eye, is its main
food source. It comes onto the land periodically,
but the reason for this is not known.

speciesData.name: Ambipom
speciesData.flavor_text:
To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails.
It rarely uses its arms now.

speciesData.name: Drifloon
speciesData.flavor_text:
If for some reason its body bursts, its soul spills
out with a screaming sound.

speciesData.name: Drifblim
speciesData.flavor_text:
Even while under careful observation, large
flocks of Drifblim flying at dusk will inexplicably
disappear from view.

speciesData.name: Buneary
speciesData.flavor_text:
When it senses danger, it perks up its ears.
On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into
its fur.

speciesData.name: Lopunny
speciesData.flavor_text:
The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched
roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

speciesData.name: Mismagius
speciesData.flavor_text:
Mismagius have been known to cast spells to
make people fall in love, so some people search
for this Pokémon as if their life depended on it.

speciesData.name: Honchkrow
speciesData.flavor_text:
If its Murkrow cronies fail to catch food for it,
or if it feels they have betrayed it, it will hunt
them down wherever they are and punish them.

speciesData.name: Glameow
speciesData.flavor_text:
When it’s happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful
movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

speciesData.name: Purugly
speciesData.flavor_text:
To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly
cinches its waist with its twin tails.

speciesData.name: Chingling
speciesData.flavor_text:
There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops,
the orb bounces all over and makes a
ringing sound.

speciesData.name: Stunky
speciesData.flavor_text:
It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its
rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

speciesData.name: Skuntank
speciesData.flavor_text:
It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells
worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

speciesData.name: Bronzor
speciesData.flavor_text:
Implements shaped like it were discovered in
ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

speciesData.name: Bronzong
speciesData.flavor_text:
Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong
for rain was the way to make crops grow.

speciesData.name: Bonsly
speciesData.flavor_text:
From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from
its body. This liquid is similar in composition to
human sweat.

speciesData.name: Mime Jr.
speciesData.flavor_text:
It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe
cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

speciesData.name: Happiny
speciesData.flavor_text:
It’s too small to lay eggs yet. As a surrogate,
it searches out round white stones.

speciesData.name: Chatot
speciesData.flavor_text:
It can learn and speak human words. If they gather,
they all learn the same saying.

speciesData.name: Spiritomb
speciesData.flavor_text:
It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as
punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

speciesData.name: Gible
speciesData.flavor_text:
It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy
passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The
force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

speciesData.name: Gabite
speciesData.flavor_text:
Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in
its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the
jewels it’s amassed or Carbink it has caught.

speciesData.name: Garchomp
speciesData.flavor_text:
The protuberances on its head serve as
sensors. It can even detect distant prey.

speciesData.name: Munchlax
speciesData.flavor_text:
When it finds something that looks like it might
be edible, it goes right ahead and swallows it
whole. That’s why it gets fatter day by day.

speciesData.name: Riolu
speciesData.flavor_text:
It’s tough enough to run right through the night,
and it’s also a hard worker, but it’s still just
a youngster.

speciesData.name: Lucario
speciesData.flavor_text:
They can detect the species of a living being—
and its emotions—from over half a mile away.
They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.

speciesData.name: Hippopotas
speciesData.flavor_text:
It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from
germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

speciesData.name: Hippowdon
speciesData.flavor_text:
It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its
body to create a towering twister for attack.

speciesData.name: Skorupi
speciesData.flavor_text:
It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey.
Its tail claws can inject its prey with a
savage poison.

speciesData.name: Drapion
speciesData.flavor_text:
It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap
of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

speciesData.name: Croagunk
speciesData.flavor_text:
Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd
sound and hits flinching opponents with a
poison jab.

speciesData.name: Toxicroak
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a
scratch could prove fatal.

speciesData.name: Carnivine
speciesData.flavor_text:
It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey
with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

speciesData.name: Finneon
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its double tail fins propel its energetic jumps.
When it breaks the surface of the sea, Wingull
swoop down to grab it on the fly.

speciesData.name: Lumineon
speciesData.flavor_text:
This deep-sea Pokémon lives at the bottom of
the sea. Its fins haul it over the seabed in
search of its favorite food—Starmie.

speciesData.name: Mantyke
speciesData.flavor_text:
When it swims close to the surface of the ocean,
people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern
on its back.

speciesData.name: Snover
speciesData.flavor_text:
In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of
frozen treats around its belly.

speciesData.name: Abomasnow
speciesData.flavor_text:
It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually
covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping
up blizzards.

speciesData.name: Weavile
speciesData.flavor_text:
They dwell in cold places. This Pokémon’s main
food source in Alola is Vulpix and Sandshrew,
which they carefully divide among their group.

speciesData.name: Magnezone
speciesData.flavor_text:
As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon
seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin,
while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

speciesData.name: Lickilicky
speciesData.flavor_text:
Their saliva contains lots of components that can
dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their
lick does not dissipate.

speciesData.name: Rhyperior
speciesData.flavor_text:
It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its
muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at
rare times.

speciesData.name: Tangrowth
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm
season, you can’t even see its eyes.

speciesData.name: Electivire
speciesData.flavor_text:
When it gets excited, it thumps its chest. With
every thud, thunder roars and electric sparks
shower all around.

speciesData.name: Magmortar
speciesData.flavor_text:
From its arm, it launches fireballs hotter than
3,500 degrees Fahrenheit. Its arm starts to
melt when it fires a whole barrage.

speciesData.name: Togekiss
speciesData.flavor_text:
It shares many blessings with people who respect
one another’s rights and avoid needless strife.

speciesData.name: Yanmega
speciesData.flavor_text:
This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of
transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail
help it stay balanced.

speciesData.name: Leafeon
speciesData.flavor_text:
The younger they are, the more they smell like
fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on
the odor of fallen leaves.

speciesData.name: Glaceon
speciesData.flavor_text:
It freezes its fur into icicles, spiky and sharp,
and tackles its prey.

speciesData.name: Gliscor
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to
carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do
the rest.

speciesData.name: Mamoswine
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population
thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

speciesData.name: Porygon-Z
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its program was modified to facilitate
extra-dimensional activities, but that led to
noticeably strange behavior.

speciesData.name: Gallade
speciesData.flavor_text:
A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights
using extending swords on its elbows.

speciesData.name: Probopass
speciesData.flavor_text:
The main body controls three mobile units called
Mini-Noses, which it maneuvers to catch prey.

speciesData.name: Dusknoir
speciesData.flavor_text:
The antenna on its head captures radio waves from
the world of spirits that command it to take
people there.

speciesData.name: Froslass
speciesData.flavor_text:
The soul of a woman lost on a snowy mountain
possessed an icicle, becoming this Pokémon.
The food it most relishes is the souls of men.

form_descriptions.description:
Forms have different signature moves and types, and the appliance forms' stats are different from the normal form's.  In Generation IV, all forms are Electric/Ghost type.

When switching forms, the old signature move (if any) is removed and the new one must be learned, overwriting another move if need be, or the switch will be cancelled; however, it can be forgotten while in the new form.  If Rotom only knows its signature move upon reverting to its default form, it learns thunder shock to avoid having no moves.

Appliances for switching Rotom's form can be found in the following locations, depending on the game:

* Platinum: In the Team Galactic Eterna Building.  Requires a secret key.
* HeartGold and SoulSilver: In the Silph Co. Office Building.  Enter the building when walking with Rotom and enter the broken elevator.
* Black and White 1 & 2: In Shopping Mall Nine.  Found in boxes in a storage room on the first floor on the far right.

speciesData.name: Rotom
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to
infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

speciesData.name: Uxie
speciesData.flavor_text:
It is said that its emergence gave humans the
intelligence to improve their quality of life.

speciesData.name: Mesprit
speciesData.flavor_text:
It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to
leave its body to fly on the lake’s surface.

speciesData.name: Azelf
speciesData.flavor_text:
It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came
from the same egg.

speciesData.name: Dialga
speciesData.flavor_text:
It has the power to control time. It appears in
Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

speciesData.name: Palkia
speciesData.flavor_text:
It has the ability to distort space. It is described as
a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

speciesData.name: Heatran
speciesData.flavor_text:
Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its
body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

speciesData.name: Regigigas
speciesData.flavor_text:
There is an enduring legend that states this
Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

form_descriptions.description:
Forms have different stats and can learn different moves from tutors.  Moves are retained through form changes.  Giratina transforms into Origin Forme in the distortion world or while holding a griseous orb.  Otherwise, it assumes its Altered Forme.

In Generation IV, the Griseous Orb returns to the bag upon entering the Wi-Fi Club or the Union Room.

speciesData.name: Giratina
speciesData.flavor_text:
It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed
upon the old world from the Distortion World.

speciesData.name: Cresselia
speciesData.flavor_text:
Those who sleep holding Cresselia’s feather are
assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent
the crescent moon.

speciesData.name: Phione
speciesData.flavor_text:
It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it
was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

speciesData.name: Manaphy
speciesData.flavor_text:
It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits
it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

speciesData.name: Darkrai
speciesData.flavor_text:
It can lull people to sleep and make them dream.
It is active during nights of the new moon.

form_descriptions.description:
Forms have different stats and can learn different moves.  Moves are retained through form changes.  Shaymin transforms into Sky Forme with the use of a gracidea.  It is limited to Land Forme at night, when frozen, and in the storage system boxes; under these conditions, Sky Shaymin reverts to Land Forme, and the Gracidea has no effect.  The Gracidea must be used again to return to Sky Forme.

In Generation IV, Shaymin is also limited to Land Forme in the Wi-Fi Club and the Union Room.

A Gracidea may be received by showing a Shaymin met in a fateful encounter to a certain NPC, depending on the game:

* Platinum: A woman in southwest floaroma town.
* HeartGold and SoulSilver: The owner of the goldenrod city flower shop.
* Black and White: A woman in the lacunosa town Pokémon Center.
* Black 2 and White 2: A woman in the striaton city Pokémon Center.

speciesData.name: Shaymin
speciesData.flavor_text:
The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the
power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are
the message it delivers.

form_descriptions.description: Form changes along with type to match a held Plate, due to multitype.

speciesData.name: Arceus
speciesData.flavor_text:
It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born
before the universe even existed.
